content: Rhys is a name of Welsh origin that means "enthusiasm" or "passion." People with the name Rhys are often described as confident, adventurous, and passionate individuals who have a natural talent for leadership and creative pursuits. They are also known for their intelligence, wit, and sense of humor. Rhys is a unique and strong name with a positive connotation, and it has been a popular choice for parents who want to give their child a distinctive and meaningful name.
